other_tests.findings: The gallbladder is distended. Multiple, shadowing stones are noted. One stone is noted at the neck of the gallbladder which did not move with decubitus positioning. The gallbladder wall measures 4-5 mm in thickness. The hepatic parenchyma is hyperechoic with area of sparing adjacent to the gallbladder fossa. No focal liver mass. No intrahepatic biliary dilation.
